# Docker Build Fixes Applied

## Problems Fixed:

1. ✅ mmcv/mmdet/mmpose compilation errors
   → Removed (not in official MuseTalk requirements)

2. ✅ 1GB+ build context transfer  
   → Added .dockerignore in project root

3. ✅ PyTorch re-downloading on every build
   → Reordered layers: copy requirements BEFORE PyTorch install

4. ✅ BuildKit cache mount failures
   → Removed --mount=type=cache for compatibility

5. ✅ README.md missing error
   → Removed from setup.py and pyproject.toml

6. ✅ pip install -e . failures
   → Removed (not needed, direct imports work)

## Current Build Should Succeed:

- First build: 15-20 minutes (~5GB downloads)
- Code changes: 1-2 minutes (cached layers)
- No compilation (prebuilt wheels only)
- Verification step catches import errors early

## Build Command:

From project root:
  make build-gpu

Or manually:
  docker build -f gpu-worker/Dockerfile -t avatar-gpu-worker:latest gpu-worker
